el. In this book, a balance is found between affective and cognitive aspects of the conscience. Accessibly written and incorporating case studies and detailed notation throughout, this is a highly practical work ideal for psychoanalysts, psychiatrists, psychologists, students and professionals working with children, adolescents and adults"--cProvided by publisher.  aTranslated from the Dutch.  a16 0aEmotions in adolescence. 0aConscience. 0aSelf-consciousness (Sensitivity) 0aAdolescence.  aBF 724.3 E5 S3313 2015c1hUAAU-Bi0162035168382  aBF 724.3 E5 S3313 2015wLCc1i0162035168382lON_SHELFmUAAUGp$150.00rYsYtBOOKu10/17/201401ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n85052651bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/113737452